solutions.content:
* What is Dijkstra Algorithm and where to apply
Dijkstra Algorithm aims to solve problem in a directed/undirected & weighted (weights are bigger than 0) graph, from source to all nodes with optimal path and cost.

* How does it work
1. creates a min heap with initial node (source node) with cost of 0
2. expand the next node in heap with smallest value, if this is a terminate node, then return value
3. add current node to closed, add all unclosed neighbor of this node to heap and repeat second step

In this problem a pure Dijkstra Algorithm (see this https://leetcode.com/problems/network-delay-time/description/ ) won't apply, because we are not necessarily finding the optimal solution, but should limit with K stops. Thus instead of adding explored nodes to closed set, we check if current count is over K.

```
class Solution {

    /**
    Dijkstra shortest weighted distance
    */
    public int findCheapestPrice(int n, int[][] flights, int src, int dst, int K) {
        Map<Integer, Map<Integer, Integer>> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int[] flight : flights) {
            int from = flight[0];
            int to = flight[1];
            int price = flight[2];
            map.putIfAbsent(from, new HashMap<>());
            map.get(from).put(to, price);
        }
        // place, cost
        PriorityQueue<int[]> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) ->  a[1] - b[1] );
        pq.offer(new int[]{ src, 0, 0 });
        while (!pq.isEmpty()) {
            int[] current = pq.poll();
            int city = current[0];
            int cost = current[1];
            int count = current[2];
            if (count > K + 1) continue;
            if (city == dst) {
                return cost;
            }
            if (map.containsKey(city)) {
                Map<Integer, Integer> nexts = map.get(city);
                for (int nextCity : nexts.keySet()) {
                    pq.offer(new int[]{ nextCity, cost + nexts.get(nextCity), count + 1 });
                }
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }

}
```

