# **Same Approach Used in Fibonacci Series**
**Starting three values of the series are given**
*Zeroth = 0
First = 1
Second = 1*

*For Third->
Previously Zeroth = 0, First = 1, Second = 1;
Third = zeroth + first + second = 0 + 1 + 1
values for next iteration will change as Zeroth, First, Second will move one step forward
Zeroth = First = 1
First = Second = 1
Second = Third = 2*

*For Forth->
Forth = zeroth + first + second = 1 + 1 + 2 = 4
values for next iteration will change as Zeroth, First, Second will move one step forward
Zeroth = First = 1
First = Second = 2
Second = Forth = 4*

**... Series Goes On**

**See the Iterative Approach.. Code is same as above explaination**

***Iterative [ACCEPTED]***
```
class Solution {
public:
    int tribonacci(int n) {
        int zeroth = 0, first = 1, second = 1, res;
        if(n < 2)       return n;
        if(n == 2)      return 1;
        for(int i = 3; i <= n; i++){
            res = zeroth + first + second;
            zeroth = first;
            first = second;
            second = res;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
***Recursive Solution [TLE]***
```
class Solution {
public:
    int tribonacci(int n){
        if(n < 2)   return n;
        if(n == 2)  return 1;
        return tribonacci(n-1) + tribonacci(n-2) + tribonacci(n-3);
};
```

***Memoization [ACCEPTED]***
