solutions.content:
**Explanation and intuition** :
* At first, the noticing fact are the problem contraints. Both m and n are less than or equals to 8.
* Also, we have to keep a track of the subset from the mentors array who have been already assigned to a particular student (can be done in the other way too).
* Thus, these facts enhance our idea that we can use DP with bitmasks. 
* At first, make two vectors to store for each student and mentor their answer sum in decimal (as n<=8, the number will definitely fit in int).
* e.g., [1,0,1,0,0] for a student turns 16+4=20
* For a mentor with [1,0,0,0,1], the sum is 16+1=17
* Thus, doing ```__builtin_popcount``` of XOR of the two sums, we get number of different bits. So just subtract it from n to get the compatibility score !

* Now, coming to DP, let we will be assigning each student a particular mentor one by one. 
* Thus, f(index,mentors) -> max compatibility score for assigning students from index till end when the mentors present in "mentors" have already been assigned. 
* Let, mentor 1,2,5 have been assigned among 5 mentors. We can keep track using mask 10011 having set bits indicating the already assigned mentors (starting from right, 0-based indexing)
* Thus, state change from index to index+1 happens ->
		From 1 to m, when that bit of the mask is unset. We just set it, add the compatibility score and call for next index.
		Finally, we take the max of all the sums !

	**The code :**

	```class Solution {
public:

    int dp[9][1<<8];

    int f(vector<int> &s_sum, vector<int> &t_sum, int index, int mask, int m, int n){
        // from this index with mask 'mask', find the max result

        if (index==m){
            return 0;
        }

        if (dp[index][mask]!=-1) return dp[index][mask];

        int ans=0;

        for (int j=0;j<m;j++){
            // which teacher
            if (mask & (1<<j)) continue;
            // mask set

            int s_score=s_sum[index];
            int t_score=t_sum[j];
            int temp=s_score^t_score;
            int to_add=n-(__builtin_popcount(temp));
            // number of same bits

            ans=max(ans, to_add + f(s_sum, t_sum, index+1, mask|(1<<j), m, n));
        }

        return dp[index][mask]=ans;
    }

    int maxCompatibilitySum(vector<vector<int>>& students, vector<vector<int>>& mentors) {
        int m=students.size();
        int n=students[0].size();

        vector<int> s_sum(m,0);
        for (int i=0;i<m;i++){
            int sum=0;
            for (int j=0;j<n;j++){
                sum=sum*2;
                sum+=students[i][j];
            }
            s_sum[i]=sum;
        }
        // [6,5,1] for example 1

        vector<int> t_sum(m,0);
        for (int i=0;i<m;i++){
            int sum=0;
            for (int j=0;j<n;j++){
                sum*=2;
                sum+=mentors[i][j];
            }
            t_sum[i]=sum;
        }
        // [4,1,6] for example 1

        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));

        int res=f(s_sum,t_sum,0,0,m,n);

        return res;
    }
};```

**Time complexity** :

Time complexity in DP : No. of states * transition time between states 

Here, no. of states = No. of indices * Total possible mask size
							= m*(2^m)
Transition time is in order of O(m), basically work done in each state

Precomputation time of binary to decimal conversion : O(m*n)

Thus total complexity : O(m*n) + O((m^2) * (2^m)) = O(m^2 * 2^m)

**Hope you like it !**

