# Intuition
for every student we will try all possibiites and all possibilites means factorial n which boils down our thinking to use bitmask and backtracking 

# Approach
now we will make a bitmask which will tell me the available mentors currently and we will make a solve function to take the maximum values of all 
in solve function we need a index which will tell me the current student for which i am alloting the mentor and using bitmask i wll check which mentors are available and add there score to the count using the comp function and call the function for the further indexes 
and once all mentors are alloted or all students are exhausted we reach the base case and return 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n*n!)

- Space complexity:
O(n) due to the recursive stack space and the bitmask.

