# Intuition
This is a simple Backtrack Problem

# Approach
1.First we will be taking final compatibility , total questions , total students and taken (mentors) as global.
2.In the main body we will find out the length of row and column of studnet array , row will become totalstudents and columns will become totalquestions.
3.We will fill the taken array with 0 and call our recursive functions passin students,mentors ,student(row),compatibilty.
4.Finally will return our finalcompatibility

5.In our recursive function we will check if our student no exceeds or becomes equal to student length we will find the max compatibility.
6.Then we will perform our recursion , if menotr is not visted we will mark it visited and find the compability count of student and mentor to getcomp recursive function.
7.Then we will call the recursive function passing studdents ,mentors,row+1,prev compatibiity + new compability.
8.While backtracking we will mark the taken[i]=0.

9.In getcomp function we will find the compability score betwee students and mentor. 



# Code
```
class Solution {
    int finalcompatibility;
    int taken[]=new int[8];
    int totalstudents,totalquestions;
    public int maxCompatibilitySum(int[][] students, int[][] mentors) {
        this.finalcompatibility=0;
        int m = students.length;
        int n = students[0].length;
        this.totalstudents = m;
        this.totalquestions = n;
        Arrays.fill(taken,0);
        getmaxcomp(students,mentors,0,0);
        return this.finalcompatibility;
    }

    private void getmaxcomp(int[][] students, int[][] mentors,int m ,int comp){
        if(m>=this.totalstudents){
            this.finalcompatibility = Math.max(comp,this.finalcompatibility);
        }

        for(int i=0;i<this.totalstudents;i++){
            if(taken[i]==0){
                taken[i]=1;
                int tempcomp = getcomp(students[m],mentors[i]);
                getmaxcomp(students,mentors,m+1,comp+tempcomp);
                taken[i]=0;
            }
        }
    }

    private int getcomp(int students[],int mentors[]){
        int count=0;
        for(int i=0;i<students.length;i++){
            if(students[i]==mentors[i])count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

