```
The mask value begins at 0. 
when jth bit of mask is 0, it means jth element is unused.
How to check whether the jth bit value is 0 ?
With bitwise trick for the mask, the jth bit == mask & (1 << j)
```
```
def maxCompatibilitySum(self, ss: List[List[int]], ms: List[List[int]]) -> int:
	m, n = len(ss), len(ss[0])
	ss = [reduce(ior, [1<<i for i in range(n) if s[i]] or [0]) for s in ss]
	ms = [reduce(ior, [1<<i for i in range(n) if m[i]] or [0]) for m in ms]
	score = [[n-(ss[i]^ms[j]).bit_count() for j in range(m)] for i in range(m)]

	@lru_cache(None)
	def dfs(i, mask):
		if i == m:
			return 0
		return max(dfs(i+1, mask | (1 << j)) + score[i][j] for j in range(m) if not mask & (1 << j))

	return dfs(0, 0)
```

